# Tokens

## Spacing Tokens

Control vertical separation and layout spacing for figures.

| Token                     | Description                                  | Default Value            |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `--figure-spacing-top`    | Top margin (automatic responsive scaling)    | `var(--content-spacing)` |
| `--figure-spacing-bottom` | Bottom margin (automatic responsive scaling) | `var(--content-spacing)` |

## Container Styling Tokens

Optional visual isolation through backgrounds and borders (defaults to minimal appearance).

| Token                        | Description                            | Default Value                     |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| `--figure-background`        | Background color                       | `transparent`                     |
| `--figure-background-dark`   | Background color for dark mode         | `transparent`                     |
| `--figure-border-width`      | Border thickness                       | `0`                               |
| `--figure-border-color`      | Border color                           | `var(--border-color-subtle)`      |
| `--figure-border-color-dark` | Border color for dark mode             | `var(--border-color-subtle-dark)` |
| `--figure-border-radius`     | Corner rounding                        | `var(--border-radius-default)`    |
| `--figure-padding`           | Internal padding around figure content | `0`                               |

## Content Layout Tokens

Control figure content positioning and width constraints.

| Token                                | Description                      | Default Value |
| ------------------------------------ | -------------------------------- | ------------- |
| `--figure-content-display`           | Display type for figure content  | `block`       |
| `--figure-content-max-width`         | Maximum width for figure content | `100%`        |
| `--figure-content-margin-horizontal` | Horizontal margins for centering | `auto`        |

## Caption Layout and Typography Tokens

Layout and typography styling for figure captions (inherits from caption and label tokens).

| Token                          | Description                                   | Default Value                        |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `--figure-caption-font-family` | Font family for captions                      | `var(--caption-font-family)`         |
| `--figure-caption-font-size`   | Font size for captions                        | `var(--caption-font-size)`           |
| `--figure-caption-color`       | Text color (automatic dark mode)              | `var(--caption-color)`               |
| `--figure-caption-spacing-top` | Gap between image and caption                 | `calc(var(--content-spacing) * 0.5)` |
| `--figure-caption-line-height` | Line height for caption text                  | `var(--line-height-sm)`              |
| `--figure-caption-text-align`  | Text alignment (left, center, right, justify) | `left`                               |
| `--figure-caption-max-width`   | Maximum width for caption text                | `100%`                               |
| `--figure-label-font-weight`   | Font weight for figure labels                 | `var(--label-font-weight)`           |
| `--figure-label-font-style`    | Font style for figure labels                  | `var(--label-font-style)`            |

# Usage

## Figure Structure

Figures combine visual content (images, charts, diagrams) with descriptive captions. The theming system provides:

**Vertical spacing**: Figures use `--figure-spacing-top` and `--figure-spacing-bottom` based on `--content-spacing`, ensuring automatic responsive and print scaling without explicit media queries.

**Optional isolation**: By default, figures have transparent backgrounds and no borders for a clean, minimal appearance. Theme authors can add visual separation through `--figure-background` and `--figure-border-*` tokens.

**Caption hierarchy**: Captions use smaller font sizes and secondary text colors to create clear visual hierarchy. Labels (e.g., "Figure 1") receive bold or italic emphasis through semantic label tokens.

**Responsive behavior**: All spacing tokens automatically scale with document rhythm through `--content-spacing` calculations, providing proper proportions across desktop, tablet, mobile, and print without manual breakpoints.

## Caption Layout

Caption styling supports both single and multi-paragraph captions:

**First paragraph**: No top margin, aligning with the figcaption spacing from the image.

**Subsequent paragraphs**: Use `--figure-caption-spacing-top` to maintain consistent spacing, similar to the pattern used in list items.

**Typography**: Captions inherit from semantic caption tokens (`--caption-font-family`, `--caption-font-size`, `--caption-color`) which provide automatic dark mode support.

## Integration with Semantic Tokens

Figures integrate with the design system's token architecture:

- **Automatic responsive behavior**: Spacing uses `--content-spacing` calculations which provide desktop, tablet, mobile, and print scaling automatically
- **Surface integration**: Optional backgrounds use `--surface-*` tokens for consistent layering
- **Border consistency**: Border colors reference semantic `--border-color-subtle` ensuring visual harmony
- **Caption integration**: Caption tokens provide shared styling with table captions for consistency

## Customization Patterns

**Minimal figures** (default): Transparent background, no borders, just spacing and captions.

**Isolated figures**: Add subtle backgrounds and borders to create visual containers for important figures.

**Centered captions**: Change `--figure-caption-text-align` to `center` for symmetrical layouts.

**Compact figures**: Reduce spacing tokens for documentation or high-density layouts.

